==English==

===Verb===
'''[[tuck]] [[in]]'''
#{{idiom}} (''transitive'') To pull the [[blankets]] up and over somebody 
# (''by extension''), to see somebody into [[bed]] or wish somebody good night.
#:''She '''tucked in''' her young son and turned out the light.''
#{{idiom}} To start to eat
#:''Tuck in, before the food goes cold.''